'''Barry Moltz''' is an American author and speaker in [[small business]] and [[entrepreneurship]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/why-unpaid-interns-dont-equal-free-work/ | title=Why Unpaid Interns Don't Equal Free Work | publisher=CBS News | date=20 July 2011 | accessdate=4 May 2014 | author=Stillman, Jessica}}</ref> He is a member of the ''Entrepreneurship Hall of Fame'',<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.theehalloffame.com/induction_committee.html | title=2013 Induction Committee | publisher=The Entrepreneurship Hall of Fame | accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref> and he taught entrepreneurship as an [[adjunct professor]] at the [[Illinois Institute of Technology]]. He was featured on television and radio programs, such as [[CNBC]]’s [[The Big Idea with Donny Deutsch]], [[MSNBC]]’s [[Your Business]] and [[NPR]]’s [[The Tavis Smiley Show]], and also hosts a radio show named ''Business Insanity Talk Radio'', which is aired on [[AM560]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://tech.co/barry-moltz-business-insanity-talk-radio-2012-03 | title=Barry Moltz Business Insanity Talk Radio | publisher=Tech | date=2 March 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref> He is a regular writer for the American Express OPEN Forum.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.americanexpress.com/us/small-business/openforum/articles/the-hidden-costs-of-hiring-an-unpaid-intern/ | title=The Hidden Costs Of Hiring An Unpaid Intern | publisher=American Express | date=12 July 2011 | accessdate=4 May 2014 | author=Moltz, Barry}}</ref>

==Career==

He started his career at [[IBM]], where he received many awards at both the branch and regional level. He left IBM to join [[Whittman-Hart]], where he became Director of Sales, and a Member of the Executive Committee. After leaving Whittman-Hart, Moltz co-founded three start-up companies. As of 2014, Barry serves on the Board of Clearview Social.

==Conferences==

In November 2010, Barry was featured at the GrowSmartBiz Small Business Conference, organized by [[Network Solutions|Network Solutions, LLC]] and the [[Washington Business Journal]] in [[Washington D.C.]] on the topic "How Social Media Has Made Customer Service the New Marketing — Deliver or die".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/washington/blog/2010/08/customer_service_in_a_self-_service_world_with_barry_moltz_author_of_bust_a_myth.html?page=all | title=Customer service in a self-service world with Barry Moltz | publisher=[[Washington Business Journal]] | date=18 August 2010 | accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref>

In June 2012, Barry spoke at 2012 BlogWorld, a conference dedicated to [[blogging]] and the business of blogging.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nbcchicago.com/blogs/inc-well/Small-Biz-Consultant-Barry-Moltz-on-Why-You-Should-Blog-153087205.html | title=Small-Biz Consultant Barry Moltz on Why You Should Blog | publisher=NBC Chicago | date=23 May 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2014 | author=LeBret, Jabez}}</ref>

==Publications==

The following is the list of books written by Barry Moltz.

* ''You Need to Be a Little Crazy: The Truth About Starting and Growing Your Own Business''<ref name="amazon">{{cite web | url=https://www.amazon.com/Barry-J.-Moltz/e/B001JS8Q26 | title=Barry J. Moltz books | publisher=[[Amazon.com]] | accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref> (2008)
* ''Bounce! The Path to True Business Confidence''<ref name="amazon" /> (2008)
* ''BAM! Delivering Customer Service in a Self Service World''<ref name="amazon" /> (2009)
* ''Small Town Rules: How Big Brands and Small Businesses Can Prosper in a Connected Economy''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorieclark/2013/12/17/the-top-mistakes-small-businesses-make-and-how-to-avoid-them/ | title=The Top Mistakes Small Businesses Make - And How To Avoid Them | publisher=[[Forbes]] | date=17 December 2013 | accessdate=4 May 2014 | author=Clark, Dorie}}</ref> (2012)
* ''How to Get Unstuck''<ref name="amazon" /> (2014)

==Awards==

In 2001 and 2002, Moltz was chosen by ''I-Street Magazine'' as one of the ''Top 100 People of Chicago’s Hi-Tech community''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.incubator.ucf.edu/newscenter/2005_pressreleases/09-19_Invention.htm |title=3rd Annual Invention to Venture Workshop |publisher=[[University of Central Florida]] |accessdate=4 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531044258/http://www.incubator.ucf.edu/newscenter/2005_PressReleases/09-19_Invention.htm |archivedate=31 May 2010 |df= }}</ref>

